Ginóbili has dual citizenship in Argentina and Italy[6] thanks to his Marchesan descent.[7] As a result of his travels, he can speak Spanish, Italian and English fluently. In his free time, Ginóbili enjoys listening to Latin music, watching movies and traveling.[8] In 2004, he married fellow Argentine Marianela Oroño.[9] On 16 May 2010, his wife gave birth to twin boys, Dante and Nicola.[10] On 21 April 2014, his wife gave birth to their third son, Luca.[11][12]
